\par\sitem{2.} “The good and the pleasant come to a man and the thoughtful
mind turns all around them and distinguishes. The wise chooses out the good
from the pleasant, but the dull soul chooses the pleasant rather than the
getting of his good and its having.
\par
\SKT{\it sa tva\.m priy\=anpriyar\=up\=a\.m\'sca
k\=am\=anabhidhy\=ayannaciketo'tyasr\=ak\,s\=i\,h, nait\=a\.m s\,r\.nk\=a\.m vittamay\=imav\=apto
