\par\sitem{3.} “And thou, O Nachiketas, hast looked close at the objects of
desire, at pleasant things and beautiful, and thou hast cast them from thee:
thou hast not entered into the net of riches in which many men sink to
perdition.
\par
\SKT{\it d\=uramete vipar\=ite vi\,s\=uc\=i avidy\=a y\=a ca vidyeti j\~n\=at\=a, vidy\=abh\=ipsina\.m
