}
\par\sitem{13.} “When mortal man has heard, when he has grasped, when he
has forcefully separated the Righteous One from his body and won that
subtle Being, then he has delight, for he has got that which one can indeed
delight in. Verily I deem of Nachiketas as a house wide open.”
\par
\SKT{\it anyatra dharm\=adanyatr\=adharm\=adanyatr\=asm\=atk\,rt\=ak\,rt\=at, anyatra
bh\=ut\=acca bhavy\=acca yattatpa\'syasi tadvada. 14. }
\par{\it Nachiketas speaks:}
\par\sitem{14.} “Tell me of That which thou seest otherwhere than in virtue
and otherwhere than in unrighteousness, otherwhere than in the created and
the uncreated, otherwhere than in that which has been and that which shall
be.”
\par
\SKT{\it sarve ved\=a yatpadam\=amananti tap\=a\.msi sarv\=a\,ni ca yadvadanti,
yadicchanto brahmacarya\.m caranti tatte pada\.m sa\.mgrahe\,na
brav\=imyomityetat. 15. }
\par{\it Yama speaks:}
\par\sitem{15.} “The seat and goal that all the Vedas glorify and which all
austerities declare, for the desire of which men practise holy living, of That
will I tell thee in brief compass. OM is that goal, O Nachiketas.
\par
\SKT{\it etaddhyev\=ak\,sara\.m brahma etaddhyev\=ak\,sara\.m param,
etaddhyev\=ak\,sara\.m j\~n\=atv\=a yo yadicchati tasya tat. 16. }
\par\sitem{16.} “For this Syllable is Brahman, this Syllable is the Most High:
this Syllable if one know, whatsoever one shall desire, it is his.
\par
\SKT{\it etad\=alambana\.m \'sre\,s\,thametad\=alambana\.m param, etad\=alambana\.m
j\~n\=atv\=a brahmaloke mah\=iyate. 17. }
\par\sitem{17.} “This support is the best, this support is the highest, knowing
this support one grows great in the world of the Brahman.
