\par\sitem{19.} “If the slayer think that he slays, if the slain think that he is
slain, both of these have not the knowledge. This slays not, neither is He
slain.
\par
\SKT{\it a\,nora\,n\=iy\=anmahato mah\=iy\=an\=atm\=asya jantornihito guh\=ay\=am,
tamakratu\,h pa\'syati v\=ita\'soko dh\=atupras\=ad\=anmahim\=anam\=atmana\,h. 20. }
\par\sitem{20.} “Finer than the fine, huger than the huge the Self hides in the
secret heart of the creature: when a man strips himself of will and is weaned
from sorrow, then he beholds Him; purified from the mental elements he sees
the greatness of the Self-being.
