\par\sitem{17.} “The Purusha, the Spirit within, who is no larger than the
finger of a man is seated for ever in the heart of creatures: one must
separate Him with patience from one's own body as one separates from a
blade of grass its main fibre. Thou shalt know Him for the Bright Immortal,
yea, for the Bright Immortal.”
\par
\SKT{\it m\,rtyuprokt\=a\.m naciketo'tha labdhv\=a vidy\=amet\=a\.m yogavidhi\.m ca
k\,rtsnam, brahmapr\=apto virajo'bh\=udvim\,rtyuranyo'pyeva\.m yo
